1780418309818893	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqhI		item.create	bn-sdv4	{"description":"Split out from bn-2ksp (done). bn-2ksp shipped the refuse-if-dirty +\n--allow-dirty half and corrected the printed hint, but the DEEPER half\n(BUG 2) was deferred and never got its own bone. This is it.\n\nPROBLEM\n`maw migrate --allow-dirty` correctly pins the dropped uncommitted work\nto a recovery ref at refs/manifold/recovery/default/<ts> (a commit whose\ntree contains the changes — Prime Invariant upheld). Its success message\nsays: \"Recovery snapshots from migration are preserved under\nrefs/manifold/recovery/ — list via `maw ws recover`.\"\n\nBut `maw ws recover` (both the bare list AND `maw ws recover default`)\nreports \"No destroyed workspaces with snapshots found\" — it only consults\nDESTROY records, not migration recovery refs. So the command migrate\npoints the user to LIES: it says the work is gone. It is recoverable, but\nonly via the undocumented:\n  git for-each-ref refs/manifold/recovery/default/\n  maw ws recover --ref <full-ref> --to <name>\n\nThis directly undermines the foundational guarantee (AGENTS.md: \"No work\nis ever lost / always check maw ws recover first\"). A user who follows\nmaw's own instructions concludes their work is lost.\n\nREPRODUCED (deterministic): notes/consolidated-sim.sh, \"migrate\" scenario,\ncurrently emits this as a soft `warn`. Verified live 2026-06-02 on\nmaw 1.0.0-pre.2: recovery ref present at refs/manifold/recovery/default/...,\n`maw ws recover` shows nothing.\n\nFIX\nMake the recover list/inspect path enumerate refs/manifold/recovery/<name>/\nrefs in addition to destroy records, so migration snapshots appear in\n`maw ws recover` and `maw ws recover <name>`, and `maw ws recover <name>\n--to <new>` resolves them. Then flip the soft `warn` in\nnotes/consolidated-sim.sh to a hard assertion.\n\nNOT a v1.0-final blocker on its own, but it's a trust-story bug on the\nflagship migrate path — should land before SG5 (bn-3ctu).\n","kind":"bug","labels":["layout","v1-0"],"size":"m","title":"maw ws recover does not surface migration recovery refs (Prime-Invariant discoverability hole)","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:8P_V-Si3UGK5q1aswl_TB_6Ff6fK4xnYxW2koQuX_Fg
